  obtained with fixed-point approach. Subsequently, the characteristics of static 
  amplification and dynamic reduction factors are analyzed. Combining the two factors 
  weighted by the dynamic-static proportion, the control performance factor on the peak 
  response is defined and optimized. Consequently, based on parametric studies, the 
  relationship between the negative stiffness parameter and dynamic-static proportion is 
  empirically formulated for practical application. Finally, the effectiveness of the 
  proposed approach is illustrated based on the numerical example for wind-induced vibration 
  control. The results have shown that the proposed approach is particularly effective for 
  the excitations dynamically characterized by low frequency and mixed with static 
  components.},
