The numerical results show that the tuned-mass damper is less effective in reducing the 
system's response when there is a high level of damping incorporated into the system. It is 
also found that the optimum tuning frequency is strongly influenced by the damping level of a 
system, especially in regard to the fixed-acceleration support motion, but the optimum 
damping ratio of the tuned-mass damper is not sensitive to the damping level of a system. The 
