  results. These parameters are functions of the TLD base amplitude. Some important 
  properties of the TLD are discussed on the basis of these results.

This paper first presents the properties of TLDs with rectangular, circular and annular tanks 
from experiments using a shaking table under sinusoidal base motions with various amplitudes 
and frequencies. Prototype-sized TLD tanks were used in the experiment to avoid hydrodynamic 
similitude problems., The wave height and the base shear force in the TLDs were measured. A 
virtual mass and a virtual damping for a TLD attached to an undamped linear SDOF structure 
were calculated from the experimental results and then amplitude-dependent equivalent mass, 
frequency and damping were obtained using the TMD analogy. Finally, some important TLD 
properties are discussed on the basis of these results.},
